 40 cm) with baking paper. Using your hands, shape 1 tablespoon of the mixture into a patty (approx. 4 cm diameter) and coat in remaining breadcrumb mixture. Place onto prepared trays and lightly spray with olive oil. Repeat with remaining mixture and breadcrumbs (makes approx. 25 patties in total)."},{"content":"Bake for 13-15 minutes (200°C) or until golden (turning them over halfway through if necessary). Serve with lemon wedges."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Be sure to include the soft bones from the tinned salmon - they're a great source of calcium.","For a dairy-free version, omit the Parmesan and replace the butter with extra virgin olive oil or virgin coconut oil.","It is not crucial to refrigerate the mixture but it does help with shaping into patties. If you prefer, you can shape the mixture into patties first, then put them into the refrigerator to firm."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 20m","25 pieces"]}